This is kind of confusing to new comers.
Long before we had a discussion in PMCI meeting to define seperate encode/decode completion code for libpldm repo instead of using spec defined PLDM completion code.
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/wiki/OpenBMC-PMCI-WG#minutes-82420

Something like,
```
enum encode_decode_rc {
	ENCODE_SUCCESS = 0xF0,
	ENCODE_FAILURE = 0xF1,
	DECODE_SUCCESS = 0xF2,
	DECODE_FAILURE = 0xF3
};
```
@Manoj/@Tom Can we add this and start using for new libpldm APIs? The existing ones can be updated later.
